3484	\begin{definition}\leanok
3485	[Step-3 equivalence sends the unit module to the unit module]
3486	  \label{def:over_restrict_unit_iso}
3487	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.overRestrictUnitIso}
3488	  \uses{def:over_restrict_equiv, lem:isIso_unitToPushforwardObjUnit_of_isIso}
3489	  \textit{The step-3 slice equivalence functor preserves the structure-sheaf (unit) module.}
3490	  Let \(U \subseteq X\) be an open subscheme. The functor of the step-3 slice
3491	  equivalence (\cref{def:over_restrict_equiv}) carries the unit
3492	  (structure-sheaf) module \(\mathbf{1}\) of the over-site
3493	  \(X.\mathrm{ringCatSheaf}.\mathrm{over}\,U\) to the unit module of
3494	  \(U.\mathrm{toScheme}.\mathrm{ringCatSheaf}\):
3495	  \[
3496	    (\mathrm{overRestrictEquiv}\,U).\mathrm{functor}.\mathrm{obj}\,
3497	      \bigl(\mathbf{1}\,(X.\mathrm{ringCatSheaf}.\mathrm{over}\,U)\bigr)
3498	      \;\cong\; \mathbf{1}\,(U.\mathrm{toScheme}.\mathrm{ringCatSheaf}) .
3499	  \]
3500	\end{definition}
3501	\begin{proof}
3502	  \uses{def:over_restrict_equiv}
3503	  By construction the functor of the equivalence is the pushforward
3504	  \(\mathrm{pushforward}\,\psi_0\) of sheaves of modules along the
3505	  over-site/open-site comparison, where \(\psi_0 = \mathrm{homMk}(\mathbf{1})\)
3506	  is the identity ring comparison. The canonical unit comparison
3507	  \(\mathrm{unitToPushforwardObjUnit}\,\psi_0 : \mathbf{1}_S \to
3508	  (\mathrm{pushforward}\,\psi_0).\mathrm{obj}\,\mathbf{1}_R\) is an isomorphism
3509	  whenever the underlying ring comparison \(\psi_0\) is one: reflecting through the
3510	  forgetful passage to presheaves (\(\mathrm{toSheaf}/\mathrm{sheafToPresheaf}\)),
3511	  its component over each object \(V\) is the functor-image of
3512	  \(\psi_0.\mathrm{app}\,V\), hence an isomorphism (this \(\mathrm{IsIso}\,\psi\)
3513	  driven criterion is supplied by the auxiliary
3514	  \(\mathrm{isIso\_unitToPushforwardObjUnit\_of\_isIso}'\)). Here
3515	  \(\psi_0 = \mathrm{homMk}(\mathbf{1})\) is the identity, so the unit comparison
3516	  is an isomorphism, and its inverse is the asserted isomorphism. (Mathlib's
3517	  isomorphism statement for \(\mathrm{unitToPushforwardObjUnit}\) instead requires
3518	  a finality hypothesis on the comparison functor; the \(\mathrm{IsIso}\,\psi\)
3519	  driven form used here is the one the slice equivalence needs.)
3520	\end{proof}
