3614	\leanok
3615	[The opens functor of an iso of schemes is an equivalence of opens sites]
3616	  \label{def:opens_map_equiv_of_iso}
3617	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.opensMapEquivOfIso}
3618	  % NOTE: the Mathlib pseudofunctoriality isos Opens.mapComp / Opens.mapId / Opens.mapIso and
3619	  % Scheme.Hom.comp_base carry no blueprint anchor; they are named in prose rather than \uses'd.
3620	  \textit{The inverse-image opens functor of a scheme isomorphism is an equivalence.}
3621	  For an isomorphism of schemes \(\varphi : Y \cong Z\), the inverse-image functor
3622	  \(\mathrm{Opens.map}\,\varphi_{\mathrm{inv}}^{\mathrm{base}} :
3623	  \mathrm{Opens}\,Y \to \mathrm{Opens}\,Z\) on opens sites is an equivalence of categories, with
3624	  inverse \(\mathrm{Opens.map}\,\varphi_{\mathrm{hom}}^{\mathrm{base}}\).
3625	\end{definition}
3626	\begin{proof}
3627	  The continuous map \(\varphi_{\mathrm{inv}}^{\mathrm{base}}\) underlying \(\varphi.\mathrm{inv}\) is
3628	  a homeomorphism, so its opens map is an equivalence. Concretely, the unit and counit isomorphisms
3629	  are assembled from the pseudofunctoriality isos \(\mathrm{Opens.mapComp}\) / \(\mathrm{Opens.mapId}\)
3630	  / \(\mathrm{Opens.mapIso}\), with the composite identities
3631	  \(\varphi_{\mathrm{hom}}^{\mathrm{base}} \circ \varphi_{\mathrm{inv}}^{\mathrm{base}} = \mathrm{id}\)
3632	  and \(\varphi_{\mathrm{inv}}^{\mathrm{base}} \circ \varphi_{\mathrm{hom}}^{\mathrm{base}} =
3633	  \mathrm{id}\) coming from \(\varphi.\mathrm{hom\_inv\_id}\) / \(\varphi.\mathrm{inv\_hom\_id}\) via
3634	  \(\mathrm{Scheme.Hom.comp\_base}\).
3635	\end{proof}
